aws::graph::propositions: # Bellanca 7ECA Aircraft Accident Information
The defining event was loss of control on ground during landing-landing roll.
A runway excursion occurred during landing-landing roll.
The pilot held a Private certificate.
The pilot was 67 years old.
The pilot was female.
The pilot had a Single-engine land airplane rating.
The pilot occupied the front seat.
The pilot had no other aircraft ratings.
The pilot had no instrument rating.
No second pilot was present.
The pilot had no instructor rating.
No toxicology was performed on the pilot.
The pilot held a Class 3 medical certification with waivers/limitations.
The pilot's last FAA medical exam was on March 13, 2013.
The pilot was not an occupational pilot.
The pilot's last flight review or equivalent was on May 3, 2013.
The pilot had 210 hours of total flight time in all aircraft.
The pilot had 210 hours of total flight time in this make and model.
The aircraft was a Bellanca 7ECA.
The aircraft registration was N5032G.
The aircraft category was Airplane.
The aircraft had a Normal airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft serial number was 1283-79.
The aircraft had a tailwheel landing gear type.
The aircraft had 2 seats.
The aircraft's last inspection was a 100-hour inspection on May 16, 2013.
The aircraft's certified maximum gross weight was 1650 pounds.
The aircraft had flown 17 hours since the last inspection.
The aircraft had 1 reciprocating engine.
The aircraft's airframe total time was 16000 hours at the time of accident.
The aircraft's engine manufacturer was LYCOMING.
The aircraft had an Emergency Locator Transmitter (ELT) installed but not activated.
The aircraft's engine model/series was O-235 SERIES.
The registered owner of the aircraft was Amelia Reid Aviation LLC.
The engine was rated at 115 Horsepower.
The operator of the aircraft was Amelia Reid Aviation LLC.
The operator held no operating certificates.
